TITLE: Paddington Bear joins Queen Elizabeth II for tea at Buckingham Palace
SUMMARY: Paddington and the queen have more in common than you might think. The two always keep a marmalade sandwich hidden away ... for emergencies.

TITLE: More than 50 people are feared dead in an attack on a Catholic church in Nigeria
SUMMARY: Gunmen opened fire and detonated explosives as worshipers were celebrating mass at the St. Francis Catholic Church in Ondo state. Several children were among the dead, a state lawmaker said.

TITLE: The first named storm of the Atlantic hurricane season floods Florida
SUMMARY: Tropical Storm Alex is heading toward Bermuda after dumping rain on parts of Florida. Alex reached tropical storm force after strengthening early Sunday.

TITLE: An upcoming trip by Pope Francis has rumors swirling about his future at the Vatican
SUMMARY: Italian and Catholic media have been rife with unsourced speculation that the 85-year-old Francis might be planning to follow in his predecessor's footsteps and step down as pope.

TITLE: The idea of working in the office, all day, every day? No thanks, say workers
SUMMARY: Working from home isn't possible in many jobs, but in companies where it is, the return to office has become a point of tension between workers and their bosses.

TITLE: Lifeguards are scarce, and it might be affecting your local pool
SUMMARY: The shortage — affecting about a third of U.S. public pools — has led some to reduce hours or close altogether. The pandemic and earlier rhetoric about work visas for foreigners led to the problem.

TITLE: 3 killed and at least 11 wounded in Philadelphia in another mass shooting
SUMMARY: Two men and a woman were among those killed in the shooting, police said. The conditions of those who were wounded by gunfire remains unknown.

TITLE: Lebanon's hospitals are running out of medicine and staff in ongoing economic crisis
SUMMARY: Hospitals are running out of medicines. Staff members are leaving. And some parents will even leave a newborn stranded in the intensive care unit if they can't afford the fees for additional care.

TITLE: A fire at a depot in Bangladesh has killed at least 49 and injured more than 100
SUMMARY: The blaze in the city of Chittagong broke out around midnight Saturday following explosions in a container full of chemicals. The cause could not immediately be determined.

TITLE: North Korea has test-fired a salvo of short-range missiles
SUMMARY: The barrage of eight missiles test-fired over 35 minutes extends a streak in weapons demonstrations this year that U.S. and South Korean officials say may culminate with a nuclear test explosion.

TITLE: Starbucks union says the coffee giant is closing a store to retaliate
SUMMARY: Starbucks gave the employees at the College Ave. location in Ithaca, N.Y., a one-week notice of the closure, the union says, with the store slated to permanently close on June 10.

TITLE: Cheeses delivered in 9 states are recalled because of potential listeria
SUMMARY: Paris Brothers, a specialty foods company based in Kansas City, Mo., is recalling several cheese products because they could have been contaminated with listeria. No illnesses have been reported.

TITLE: A small plane flew near Biden's beach house in Delaware
SUMMARY: The White House said it was apparently by mistake that a small private plane entered restricted airspace. The president and first lady were evacuated but have since returned.

TITLE: Ann Turner Cook, the original Gerber baby, dies at 95
SUMMARY: A sketch of 5-month-old Cook became the Gerber company's trademark in 1931 and has been used in all packaging and advertising since.

TITLE: Abbott's baby formula plant is reopening in a step that could soon ease the shortage
SUMMARY: Abbott's initial re-release of products will be available to consumers beginning around June 20, the company says. The facility was forced to close after a bacterial contamination at the site.
